So you mean the PFC pause frame always exists in such case?

> So you mean the PFC pause frame always exists in such case?

@bingwang-ms yes, that's right since we always flood pfc frames from the traffic generator to the DUT to congest the egress link. Effectively we should not be polling the DUT during this time when the link is congested.

Hi, @rraghav-cisco , may you share more details about "This might not work all the time.", what scenario this happens? thanks.

> Hi, @rraghav-cisco , may you share more details about "This might not work all the time.", what scenario this happens? thanks.

The original code checks if we are using the particular LC or not to find if the link is long link or not. But the same LC can be configured for short link as well, and in this case, the script will wrongly assume long-link and fail.
